com.rcextract.minecord.utils

Class Table<A,B,C>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.rcextract.minecord.utils.Table<A,B,C>
  • Type Parameters:
    A - Column a.
    B - Column b.
    C - Column c.

    public class Table<A,B,C>
extends Object
    A flexible Table with three columns. Unlike Table, this table does not treat entries like it or Map. Instead, it allows all entries except for ones that has the same A, B, and C values in another entries, which means if two entries are compared with Object.equals(Object) and it returns true, the entry will not be put. This leads to a situation which a table can have entries with the same A, same B, same C, same A and same B, same B and same C, ans same A and same C.
